onal arms dealers, and Afghan drug kingpins, he provides a powerful, eye-opening, and often heartbreaking account of military adventurism gone horribly wrong.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAfghan War, 2001-2021xCampaignszAfghanistanzHelmand. 0aAfghan War, 2001-2021xCasualtieszAfghanistanzHelmand. 0aAfghan War, 2001-2021xCasualtieszGreat Britain. 0aAfghan War, 2001-2021xEconomic aspectszGreat Britain. 0aAfghan War, 2001-2021xParticipation, British. 0aCivilian war casualtieszAfghanistanzHelmand. 7aHISTORY / Military / Afghan War (2001-).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030019062540uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030019488340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300194883423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300194883/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY